The paper introduces a new deep learning approach to cardinality estimation for databases, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.DB (databases) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (machine learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of ad-hoc queries, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (artificial intelligence) sub-category. The use of sketches and the TPC-H and IMDb datasets suggests that it may also belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the mention of visualization and estimation with other cardinality estimators suggests that it may belong to the cs.CV (computer vision and pattern recognition) sub-category.
